<!doctype html>
<meta charset="utf8">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="./spec.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/8.4/styles/github.min.css">
<script src="./spec.js"></script>
<pre class="metadata">
title: Declarations in Conditionals
stage: 1
contributors: Devin Rousso
</pre>

<emu-intro id=introduction>
  <h1>Introduction</h1>
  <p>This is the formal specification for a proposed extension of the `if` and `while` JavaScript control flow statements. It modifies the original <a href=https://tc39.es/ecma262/multipage/>ECMAScript specification</a> with several new or revised clauses. See <a href=https://github.com/tc39/proposal-Declarations-in-Conditionals/#readme>the proposal's explainer</a> for the proposal's background, motivation, and usage examples.</p>
  <p>This proposal is specified against ECMAScript as extended by the <a href=https://github.com/tc39/proposal-explicit-resource-management>Explicit Resource Management proposal</a>.</p>
</emu-intro>

<emu-clause id="sec-ecmascript-language-statements-and-declarations" number="14">
  <h1>ECMAScript Language: Statements and Declarations</h1>

  <emu-clause id="sec-if-statement" number="6">
    <h1>The `if` Statement</h1>
    <h2>Syntax</h2>
    <emu-grammar type="definition">
      IfStatement[Yield, Await, Return] :
        `if` `(` <del>Expression[+In, ?Yield, ?Await]</del><ins>IfCondition[+In, ?Yield, ?Await]</ins> `)` Statement[?Yield, ?Await, ?Return] `else` Statement[?Yield, ?Await, ?Return]
        `if` `(` <del>Expression[+In, ?Yield, ?Await]</del><ins>IfCondition[+In, ?Yield, ?Await]</ins> `)` Statement[?Yield, ?Await, ?Return] [lookahead != `else`]

      <ins class="block">
      IfCondition[In, Yield, Await] :
        Expression[?In, ?Yield, ?Await]
        LetOrConst BindingIdentifier[?Yield, ?Await] Initializer[?In, ?Yield, ?Await]
        `using` [no LineTerminator here] BindingIdentifier[?Yield, ?Await] Initializer[?In, ?Yield, ?Await]
        CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead[?Yield] [no LineTerminator here] BindingIdentifier[?Yield, ?Await] Initializer[?In, ?Yield, ?Await]
        LexicalDeclaration[?In, ?Yield, ?Await] `;` Expression[?In, ?Yield, ?Await]
      </ins>
    </emu-grammar>
    <emu-note>The lookahead-restriction [lookahead ≠ `else`] resolves the classic "dangling else" problem in the usual way. That is, when the choice of associated `if` is otherwise ambiguous, the `else` is associated with the nearest (innermost) of the candidate `if`s</emu-note>

    <emu-clause id="sec-if-statement-static-semantics-early-errors">
      <h1>Static Semantics: Early Errors</h1>
      <emu-grammar>IfStatement : `if` `(` <del>Expression</del><ins>IfCondition</ins> `)` Statement `else` Statement</emu-grammar>
      <ul>
        <li>
          It is a Syntax Error if IsLabelledFunction(the first |Statement|) is *true*.
        </li>
        <li>
          It is a Syntax Error if IsLabelledFunction(the second |Statement|) is *true*.
        </li>
        <li>
          <ins>It is a Syntax Error if any element of the BoundNames of |IfCondition| also occurs in the VarDeclaredNames of the first |Statement|.</ins>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <emu-grammar>IfStatement : `if` `(` <del>Expression</del><ins>IfCondition</ins> `)` Statement</emu-grammar>
      <ul>
        <li>
          It is a Syntax Error if IsLabelledFunction(|Statement|) is *true*.
        </li>
        <li>
          <ins>It is a Syntax Error if any element of the BoundNames of |IfCondition| also occurs in the VarDeclaredNames of |Statement|.</ins>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <emu-note>
        <p>It is only necessary to apply <del>this rule</del><ins>the IsLabelledFunction rules</ins> if the extension specified in <emu-xref href="#sec-labelled-function-declarations"></emu-xref> is implemented.</p>
      </emu-note>
      <ins>
      <emu-note>
          <p>The BoundNames of an |IfCondition| are scoped to the first |Statement|, so a `var` of the same name in second |Statement| would refer to a different variable. Disallowing this avoids the resulting ambiguity. The second |Statement| (the `else` branch, if it exists) is unaffected by these names and may freely contain a `var` of the same name.</p>
      </emu-note>
      </ins>
    </emu-clause>

    <ins class="block">
    <emu-clause id="sec-if-condition-static-semantics-boundnames" type="sdo">
      <h1>Static Semantics: BoundNames</h1>
      <emu-grammar>IfCondition : Expression</emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Return a new empty List.
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar>
        IfCondition :
          LetOrConst BindingIdentifier Initializer
          `using` BindingIdentifier Initializer
          CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead BindingIdentifier Initializer
      </emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Return the BoundNames of |BindingIdentifier|.
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar>IfCondition : LexicalDeclaration `;` Expression</emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Return the BoundNames of |LexicalDeclaration|.
      </emu-alg>
    </emu-clause>
    </ins>

    <ins class="block">
    <emu-clause id="sec-if-condition-static-semantics-isconstantdeclaration" type="sdo">
      <h1>Static Semantics: IsConstantDeclaration</h1>
      <emu-grammar>IfCondition : Expression</emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Return *false*.
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar>IfCondition : LetOrConst BindingIdentifier Initializer</emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Return IsConstantDeclaration of |LetOrConst|.
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar>
        IfCondition :
          `using` BindingIdentifier Initializer
          CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead BindingIdentifier Initializer
      </emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Return *true*.
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar>IfCondition : LexicalDeclaration `;` Expression</emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Return IsConstantDeclaration of |LexicalDeclaration|.
      </emu-alg>
    </emu-clause>
    </ins>

    <ins class="block">
    <emu-clause id="sec-runtime-semantics-ifconditiondeclarationinstantiation" type="sdo">
      <h1>
        Runtime Semantics: IfConditionDeclarationInstantiation (
          _env_: a Declarative Environment Record,
        ): ~unused~
      </h1>
      <dl class="header">
        <dt>description</dt>
        <dd>It creates the bindings declared by |IfCondition| in _env_.</dd>
      </dl>
      <emu-grammar>IfCondition : Expression</emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Return ~unused~.
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar>
        IfCondition :
          LetOrConst BindingIdentifier Initializer
          `using` BindingIdentifier Initializer
          CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead BindingIdentifier Initializer
          LexicalDeclaration `;` Expression
      </emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Let _isConst_ be IsConstantDeclaration of |IfCondition|.
        1. For each element _dn_ of the BoundNames of |IfCondition|, do
          1. If _isConst_ is *true*, then
            1. Perform ! _env_.CreateImmutableBinding(_dn_, *true*).
          1. Else,
            1. Perform ! _env_.CreateMutableBinding(_dn_, *false*).
        1. Return ~unused~.
      </emu-alg>
    </emu-clause>
    </ins>

    <emu-clause id="sec-if-statement-runtime-semantics-evaluation" type="sdo">
      <h1>Runtime Semantics: Evaluation</h1>
      <emu-grammar>IfStatement : `if` `(` <del>Expression</del><ins>IfCondition</ins> `)` Statement `else` Statement</emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. <ins>Let _oldEnv_ be the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment.</ins>
        1. <ins>If the BoundNames of |IfCondition| is not empty, then</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _ifEnv_ be NewDeclarativeEnvironment(_oldEnv_).</ins>
          1. <ins>Perform IfConditionDeclarationInstantiation of |IfCondition| with argument _ifEnv_.</ins>
          1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _ifEnv_.</ins>
        1. <ins>Else,</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _ifEnv_ be _oldEnv_.</ins>
        1. Let _exprRef_ be <ins>Completion(</ins>Evaluation of <del>|Expression|</del><ins>|IfCondition|)</ins>.
        1. <ins>If _exprRef_ is a normal completion, set _exprRef_ to Completion(GetValue(_exprRef_.[[Value]])).</ins>
        1. <ins>If _exprRef_ is an abrupt completion, then</ins>
          1. <ins>If _ifEnv_ is not _oldEnv_, then</ins>
            1. <ins>Set _exprRef_ to Completion(DisposeResources(_ifEnv_.[[DisposeCapability]], _exprRef_)).</ins>
            1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _oldEnv_.</ins>
          1. <ins>Return ? _exprRef_.</ins>
        1. Let _exprValue_ be ToBoolean(<del>? GetValue(_exprRef_)</del><ins>_exprRef_.[[Value]]</ins>).
        1. If _exprValue_ is *true*, then
          1. Let _stmtCompletion_ be Completion(Evaluation of the first |Statement|).
          1. <ins>If _ifEnv_ is not _oldEnv_, then</ins>
            1. <ins>Set _stmtCompletion_ to Completion(DisposeResources(_ifEnv_.[[DisposeCapability]], _stmtCompletion_)).</ins>
            1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _oldEnv_.</ins>
        1. Else,
          1. <ins>If _ifEnv_ is not _oldEnv_, then</ins>
            1. <ins>Let _disposeCompletion_ be Completion(DisposeResources(_ifEnv_.[[DisposeCapability]], NormalCompletion(*undefined*))).</ins>
            1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _oldEnv_.</ins>
            1. <ins>If _disposeCompletion_ is an abrupt completion, return ? _disposeCompletion_.</ins>
          1. Let _stmtCompletion_ be Completion(Evaluation of the second |Statement|).
        1. Return ? UpdateEmpty(_stmtCompletion_, *undefined*).
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar>IfStatement : `if` `(` <del>Expression</del><ins>IfCondition</ins> `)` Statement</emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. <ins>Let _oldEnv_ be the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment.</ins>
        1. <ins>If the BoundNames of |IfCondition| is not empty, then</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _ifEnv_ be NewDeclarativeEnvironment(_oldEnv_).</ins>
          1. <ins>Perform IfConditionDeclarationInstantiation of |IfCondition| with argument _ifEnv_.</ins>
          1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _ifEnv_.</ins>
        1. <ins>Else,</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _ifEnv_ be _oldEnv_.</ins>
        1. Let _exprRef_ be <ins>Completion(</ins>Evaluation of <del>|Expression|</del><ins>|IfCondition|)</ins>.
        1. <ins>If _exprRef_ is a normal completion, set _exprRef_ to Completion(GetValue(_exprRef_.[[Value]])).</ins>
        1. <ins>If _exprRef_ is an abrupt completion, then</ins>
          1. <ins>If _ifEnv_ is not _oldEnv_, then</ins>
            1. <ins>Set _exprRef_ to Completion(DisposeResources(_ifEnv_.[[DisposeCapability]], _exprRef_)).</ins>
            1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _oldEnv_.</ins>
          1. <ins>Return ? _exprRef_.</ins>
        1. Let _exprValue_ be ToBoolean(<del>? GetValue(_exprRef_)</del><ins>_exprRef_.[[Value]]</ins>).
        1. If _exprValue_ is *false*, then
          1. <ins>If _ifEnv_ is not _oldEnv_, then</ins>
            1. <ins>Perform ? DisposeResources(_ifEnv_.[[DisposeCapability]], NormalCompletion(*undefined*)).</ins>
            1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _oldEnv_.</ins>
          1. Return *undefined*.
        1. Else,
          1. Let _stmtCompletion_ be Completion(Evaluation of |Statement|).
          1. <ins>If _ifEnv_ is not _oldEnv_, then</ins>
            1. <ins>Set _stmtCompletion_ to Completion(DisposeResources(_ifEnv_.[[DisposeCapability]], _stmtCompletion_)).</ins>
            1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _oldEnv_.</ins>
          1. Return ? UpdateEmpty(_stmtCompletion_, *undefined*).
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar>IfCondition : Expression</emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. Return ? Evaluation of |Expression|.
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar><ins>IfCondition : LetOrConst BindingIdentifier Initializer</ins></emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. <ins>Let _bindingId_ be the StringValue of |BindingIdentifier|.</ins>
        1. <ins>Let _lhs_ be ! ResolveBinding(_bindingId_).</ins>
        1. <ins>If IsAnonymousFunctionDefinition(|Initializer|) is *true*, then</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _value_ be ? NamedEvaluation of |Initializer| with argument _bindingId_.</ins>
        1. <ins>Else,</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _rhs_ be ? Evaluation of |Initializer|.</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _value_ be ? GetValue(_rhs_).</ins>
        1. <ins>Perform ! InitializeReferencedBinding(_lhs_, _value_, ~normal~).</ins>
        1. <ins>Return _value_.</ins>
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar><ins>IfCondition : `using` BindingIdentifier Initializer</ins></emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. <ins>Let _bindingId_ be the StringValue of |BindingIdentifier|.</ins>
        1. <ins>Let _lhs_ be ! ResolveBinding(_bindingId_).</ins>
        1. <ins>Let _rhs_ be ? Evaluation of |Initializer|.</ins>
        1. <ins>Let _value_ be ? GetValue(_rhs_).</ins>
        1. <ins>Perform ! InitializeReferencedBinding(_lhs_, _value_, ~sync-dispose~).</ins>
        1. <ins>Return _value_.</ins>
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar><ins>IfCondition : CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead BindingIdentifier Initializer</ins></emu-grammar>
      </emu-alg><emu-alg>
        1. <ins>Let _bindingId_ be the StringValue of |BindingIdentifier|.</ins>
        1. <ins>Let _lhs_ be ! ResolveBinding(_bindingId_).</ins>
        1. <ins>Let _rhs_ be ? Evaluation of |Initializer|.</ins>
        1. <ins>Let _value_ be ? GetValue(_rhs_).</ins>
        1. <ins>Perform ! InitializeReferencedBinding(_lhs_, _value_, ~async-dispose~).</ins>
        1. <ins>Return _value_.</ins>
      </emu-alg>
      <emu-grammar><ins>IfCondition : LexicalDeclaration `;` Expression</ins></emu-grammar>
      <emu-alg>
        1. <ins>Perform ? Evaluation of |LexicalDeclaration|.</ins>
        1. <ins>Return ? Evaluation of |Expression|.</ins>
      </emu-alg>
    </emu-clause>
  </emu-clause>

  <emu-clause id="sec-iteration-statements">
    <h1>Iteration Statements</h1>

    <emu-clause id="sec-while-statement" number="3">
      <h1>The `while` Statement</h1>
      <h2>Syntax</h2>
      <emu-grammar type="definition">
        WhileStatement[Yield, Await, Return] :
          `while` `(` <del>Expression[+In, ?Yield, ?Await]</del><ins>WhileCondition[+In, ?Yield, ?Await]</ins> `)` Statement[?Yield, ?Await, ?Return]

        <ins class="block">
        WhileCondition[In, Yield, Await] :
          Expression[?In, ?Yield, ?Await]
          LetOrConst BindingIdentifier[?Yield, ?Await] Initializer[?In, ?Yield, ?Await]
          `using` [no LineTerminator here] BindingIdentifier[?Yield, ?Await] Initializer[?In, ?Yield, ?Await]
          CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead[?Yield] [no LineTerminator here] BindingIdentifier[?Yield, ?Await] Initializer[?In, ?Yield, ?Await]
          LexicalDeclaration[?In, ?Yield, ?Await] `;` Expression[?In, ?Yield, ?Await]
        </ins>
      </emu-grammar>

      <emu-clause id="sec-while-statement-static-semantics-early-errors">
        <h1>Static Semantics: Early Errors</h1>
        <emu-grammar>WhileStatement : `while` `(` <del>Expression</del><ins>WhileCondition</ins> `)` Statement</emu-grammar>
        <ul>
          <li>
            It is a Syntax Error if IsLabelledFunction(|Statement|) is *true*.
          </li>
          <li>
            <ins>It is a Syntax Error if any element of the BoundNames of |WhileCondition| also occurs in the VarDeclaredNames of |Statement|.</ins>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <emu-note>
          <p>It is only necessary to apply <del>this rule</del><ins>the IsLabelledFunction rule</ins> if the extension specified in <emu-xref href="#sec-labelled-function-declarations"></emu-xref> is implemented.</p>
        </emu-note>
        <ins>
        <emu-note>
          <p>The BoundNames of a |WhileCondition| are scoped to the |Statement|, so a `var` of the same name in the |Statement| would refer to a different variable. Disallowing this avoids the resulting ambiguity.</p>
        </emu-note>
        </ins>
      </emu-clause>

      <ins class="block">
      <emu-clause id="sec-while-condition-static-semantics-boundnames" type="sdo">
        <h1>Static Semantics: BoundNames</h1>
        <emu-grammar>WhileCondition : Expression</emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Return a new empty List.
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar>
          WhileCondition :
            LetOrConst BindingIdentifier Initializer
            `using` BindingIdentifier Initializer
            CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead BindingIdentifier Initializer
        </emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Return the BoundNames of |BindingIdentifier|.
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar>WhileCondition : LexicalDeclaration `;` Expression</emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Return the BoundNames of |LexicalDeclaration|.
        </emu-alg>
      </emu-clause>
      </ins>

      <ins class="block">
      <emu-clause id="sec-while-condition-static-semantics-isconstantdeclaration" type="sdo">
        <h1>Static Semantics: IsConstantDeclaration</h1>
        <emu-grammar>WhileCondition : Expression</emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Return *false*.
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar>WhileCondition : LetOrConst BindingIdentifier Initializer</emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Return IsConstantDeclaration of |LetOrConst|.
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar>
          WhileCondition :
            `using` BindingIdentifier Initializer
            CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead BindingIdentifier Initializer
        </emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Return *true*.
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar>WhileCondition : LexicalDeclaration `;` Expression</emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Return IsConstantDeclaration of |LexicalDeclaration|.
        </emu-alg>
      </emu-clause>
      </ins>

      <ins class="block">
      <emu-clause id="sec-runtime-semantics-whileconditiondeclarationinstantiation" type="sdo">
        <h1>
          Runtime Semantics: WhileConditionDeclarationInstantiation (
            _env_: a Declarative Environment Record,
          ): ~unused~
        </h1>
        <dl class="header">
          <dt>description</dt>
          <dd>It creates the bindings declared by |WhileCondition| in _env_.</dd>
        </dl>
        <emu-grammar>WhileCondition : Expression</emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Return ~unused~.
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar>
          WhileCondition :
            LetOrConst BindingIdentifier Initializer
            `using` BindingIdentifier Initializer
            CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead BindingIdentifier Initializer
            LexicalDeclaration `;` Expression
        </emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Let _isConst_ be IsConstantDeclaration of |WhileCondition|.
          1. For each element _dn_ of the BoundNames of |WhileCondition|, do
            1. If _isConst_ is *true*, then
              1. Perform ! _env_.CreateImmutableBinding(_dn_, *true*).
            1. Else,
              1. Perform ! _env_.CreateMutableBinding(_dn_, *false*).
          1. Return ~unused~.
        </emu-alg>
      </emu-clause>
      </ins>

      <emu-clause id="sec-runtime-semantics-whileloopevaluation" oldids="sec-while-statement-runtime-semantics-labelledevaluation" type="sdo">
        <h1>
          Runtime Semantics: WhileLoopEvaluation (
            _labelSet_: a List of Strings,
          ): either a normal completion containing an ECMAScript language value or an abrupt completion
        </h1>
        <dl class="header">
        </dl>
        <emu-grammar>WhileStatement : `while` `(` <del>Expression</del><ins>WhileCondition</ins> `)` Statement</emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Let _V_ be *undefined*.
          1. <ins>Let _oldEnv_ be the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment.</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _hasDeclarations_ be *false*.</ins>
          1. <ins>If the BoundNames of |WhileCondition| is not empty, set _hasDeclarations_ to *true*.</ins>
          1. Repeat,
            1. <ins>If _hasDeclarations_ is *true*, then</ins>
              1. <ins>Let _whileEnv_ be NewDeclarativeEnvironment(_oldEnv_).</ins>
              1. <ins>Perform WhileConditionDeclarationInstantiation of |WhileCondition| with argument _whileEnv_.</ins>
              1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _whileEnv_.</ins>
            1. <ins>Else,</ins>
              1. <ins>Let _whileEnv_ be _oldEnv_.</ins>
            1. Let _exprRef_ be <ins>Completion(</ins>Evaluation of <del>|Expression|</del><ins>|WhileCondition|)</ins>.
            1. <ins>If _exprRef_ is a normal completion, set _exprRef_ to Completion(GetValue(_exprRef_.[[Value]])).</ins>
            1. <del>Let _exprValue_ be ? GetValue(_exprRef_).</del>
            1. <ins>If _exprRef_ is an abrupt completion, then</ins>
              1. <ins>If _whileEnv_ is not _oldEnv_, then</ins>
                1. <ins>Set _exprRef_ to Completion(DisposeResources(_whileEnv_.[[DisposeCapability]], _exprRef_)).</ins>
                1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _oldEnv_.</ins>
              1. <ins>Return ? _exprRef_.</ins>
            1. If <del>ToBoolean(_exprValue_) is *false*, return _V_</del><ins>ToBoolean(_exprRef_.[[Value]]) is *false*, then</ins>
              1. <ins>If _whileEnv_ is not _oldEnv_, then</ins>
                1. <ins>Perform ? DisposeResources(_whileEnv_.[[DisposeCapability]], NormalCompletion(*undefined*)).</ins>
                1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _oldEnv_.</ins>
              1. <ins>Return _V_.</ins>
            1. Let _stmtResult_ be Completion(Evaluation of |Statement|).
            1. <ins>If _whileEnv_ is not _oldEnv_, then</ins>
              1. <ins>Set _stmtResult_ to Completion(DisposeResources(_whileEnv_.[[DisposeCapability]], _stmtResult_)).</ins>
              1. <ins>Set the running execution context's LexicalEnvironment to _oldEnv_.</ins>
            1. If LoopContinues(_stmtResult_, _labelSet_) is *false*, return ? UpdateEmpty(_stmtResult_, _V_).
            1. If _stmtResult_.[[Value]] is not ~empty~, set _V_ to _stmtResult_.[[Value]].
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar>WhileCondition : Expression</emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. Return ? Evaluation of |Expression|.
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar><ins>WhileCondition : LetOrConst BindingIdentifier Initializer</ins></emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. <ins>Let _bindingId_ be the StringValue of |BindingIdentifier|.</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _lhs_ be ! ResolveBinding(_bindingId_).</ins>
          1. <ins>If IsAnonymousFunctionDefinition(|Initializer|) is *true*, then</ins>
            1. <ins>Let _value_ be ? NamedEvaluation of |Initializer| with argument _bindingId_.</ins>
          1. <ins>Else,</ins>
            1. <ins>Let _rhs_ be ? Evaluation of |Initializer|.</ins>
            1. <ins>Let _value_ be ? GetValue(_rhs_).</ins>
          1. <ins>Perform ! InitializeReferencedBinding(_lhs_, _value_, ~normal~).</ins>
          1. <ins>Return _value_.</ins>
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar><ins>WhileCondition : `using` BindingIdentifier Initializer</ins></emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. <ins>Let _bindingId_ be the StringValue of |BindingIdentifier|.</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _lhs_ be ! ResolveBinding(_bindingId_).</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _rhs_ be ? Evaluation of |Initializer|.</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _value_ be ? GetValue(_rhs_).</ins>
          1. <ins>Perform ! InitializeReferencedBinding(_lhs_, _value_, ~sync-dispose~).</ins>
          1. <ins>Return _value_.</ins>
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar><ins>WhileCondition : CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead BindingIdentifier Initializer</ins></emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. <ins>Let _bindingId_ be the StringValue of |BindingIdentifier|.</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _lhs_ be ! ResolveBinding(_bindingId_).</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _rhs_ be ? Evaluation of |Initializer|.</ins>
          1. <ins>Let _value_ be ? GetValue(_rhs_).</ins>
          1. <ins>Perform ! InitializeReferencedBinding(_lhs_, _value_, ~async-dispose~).</ins>
          1. <ins>Return _value_.</ins>
        </emu-alg>
        <emu-grammar><ins>WhileCondition : LexicalDeclaration `;` Expression</ins></emu-grammar>
        <emu-alg>
          1. <ins>Perform ? Evaluation of |LexicalDeclaration|.</ins>
          1. <ins>Return ? Evaluation of |Expression|.</ins>
        </emu-alg>
      </emu-clause>
    </emu-clause>
  </emu-clause>
</emu-clause>
